attention_ck_midsurvey: Age,Criminal History
decision_style: I followed a different strategy (please explain below):
decision_style_text: None of the metrics mattered because you're asking me to evict someone for ""office space"" which is the dumbest thing I've ever heard.  I wouldn't evict anyone and there's no way you're making me choose for a terrible reason like that.  In addition, even if were to look at the data, none of it actually matters.  You're asking me to make preference to kick someone out of their home for no tangible reason that matters.  Are they noisy? are they drug addicts? are they causing a disturbance regularly?  These kinds of things matter here, not any of the information provided.
feedback: I already gave my feedback technically in one of the previous questions but again, this was a very stupid metric to make choices on ""we need office space, kick out the homeless"".  Next time choose a better story.  In addition, the metrics are unimportant to people you've given homes to.  Unless they're destroying the home, causing disturbances, doing illegal activies, etc, there's no reason to kick someone out.  Office space is not ""much needed"" that you can kick someone out for no reason.
